## Middleware Pipeline

Use tower `ServiceBuilder` to compose middleware. Order matters — outer layers
execute first on ingress and last on egress.

```rust
use tower::ServiceBuilder;
use tower_http::trace::TraceLayer;

let app = build_router(state)
    .layer(
        ServiceBuilder::new()
            .layer(TraceLayer::new_for_http())
            // Auth middleware (inner — runs after tracing)
            .layer(middleware::from_fn_with_state(state.clone(), require_auth)),
    );
```

**Middleware order (outer → inner):**

1. Request ID assignment
2. Structured tracing/logging
3. CORS
4. Authentication
5. Rate limiting
6. Request body size limits

