## Background Tasks

Use `tokio::spawn` for lightweight async tasks. Use
`tokio::task::spawn_blocking` for CPU-heavy work or blocking I/O that would
stall the async executor.

```rust
use tokio::time::{interval, Duration};

// Lightweight periodic async task
pub fn start_token_renewal_task(vault: Arc<dyn VaultClient>) {
    tokio::spawn(async move {
        let mut ticker = interval(Duration::from_secs(600));
        loop {
            ticker.tick().await;
            if let Err(err) = vault.renew_token().await {
                tracing::error!(error = %err, "vault token renewal failed");
            }
        }
    });
}

// CPU-heavy work — offload to the blocking thread pool
pub async fn hash_password(password: String) -> Result<String, HashError> {
    tokio::task::spawn_blocking(move || {
        argon2_hash(&password)
    })
    .await
    .map_err(|_| HashError::TaskPanicked)?
}
```

**Rules:**
- Never block the async executor with `std::thread::sleep`, synchronous file I/O,
  or CPU-heavy computation
- Store task `JoinHandle`s in `AppState` if you need to cancel them on shutdown
- Log all task panics — `tokio::spawn` silently drops panics by default

