## Workspace Organisation

For multi-crate security projects, use a Cargo workspace. Each crate has a
single, clear responsibility.

```
my-security-project/
├── Cargo.toml              # Workspace manifest
├── Cargo.lock              # Committed for workspaces with binaries
├── crates/
│   ├── core/               # Domain types, traits, errors (no I/O)
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   └── Cargo.toml
│   ├── crypto/             # Encryption, decryption, key derivation
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   └── Cargo.toml
│   ├── api/                # HTTP server (Axum), handlers, middleware
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   └── Cargo.toml
│   ├── cli/                # CLI binary (clap)
│   │   ├── src/
│   │   └── Cargo.toml
│   └── ffi/                # FFI bindings (PyO3 / Neon / UniFFI)
│       ├── src/
│       └── Cargo.toml
└── .claude/
    ├── CLAUDE.md
    ├── CODING-PRINCIPLES.md
    ├── TESTING.md
    ├── SECURITY.md
    └── DEVELOPMENT.md
```

**Dependency rules:**
- `core` has no dependencies on other workspace crates
- `crypto` depends on `core`
- `api` and `cli` depend on `core` and `crypto`
- `ffi` depends on `core` and `crypto`; never on `api` or `cli`

