## Configuration

Use the `config` crate or `figment` for layered configuration. Validate all
configuration at startup — fail fast rather than failing at runtime.
{{#if has_crypto}}
Secrets come from HashiCorp Vault, never from the configuration file.
{{/if}}

```rust
use config::{Config, ConfigError, Environment, File};
use serde::Deserialize;

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize)]
pub struct AppConfig {
    pub server: ServerConfig,
    pub database: DatabaseConfig,
}

#[derive(Debug, Deserialize)]
pub struct ServerConfig {
    pub host: String,
    pub port: u16,
}

impl AppConfig {
    pub fn load() -> Result<Self, ConfigError> {
        Config::builder()
            .add_source(File::with_name("config/default"))
            .add_source(File::with_name("config/local").required(false))
            .add_source(Environment::with_prefix("APP").separator("__"))
            .build()?
            .try_deserialize()
    }
}
```

