## Dependency Injection

Prefer trait objects (`Arc<dyn Trait>`) for injectable dependencies in
`AppState`. Use generics (`<S: Service>`) only when the performance overhead of
dynamic dispatch is measured and significant.

```rust
// Preferred — simple, injectable, testable
pub struct OrderService {
    repo: Arc<dyn OrderRepository>,
    notifier: Arc<dyn Notifier>,
}

// Alternative — zero-cost abstraction, but harder to mock
pub struct OrderService<R: OrderRepository, N: Notifier> {
    repo: R,
    notifier: N,
}
```

**Rule:** Default to `Arc<dyn Trait>`. Switch to generics only after profiling
shows dynamic dispatch is a measured bottleneck.
